            <!-- Tour Description -->
            <div class="tour-description">
                <h2>Discover Agadir's Remarkable History and Modern Charm</h2>
                <p>Experience the best of Agadir with our comprehensive <strong>Agadir city tour</strong>! This half-day <strong>Agadir sightseeing tour</strong> is perfect for first-time visitors wanting to understand the city's unique history, vibrant culture, and impressive modern development. Unlike most Moroccan cities, Agadir is relatively young - rebuilt from scratch after the devastating 1960 earthquake that destroyed 90% of the old city.</p>
                
                <p>Your <strong>city tour Agadir half day</strong> takes you to all major attractions including the historic <strong>Agadir Kasbah and Medina</strong>, the bustling Souk El Had market (North Africa's largest!), beautiful modern marina, and scenic beach promenade. Your expert local guide - born and raised in Agadir - will share fascinating stories about the city's dramatic history, from the tragic earthquake to its remarkable phoenix-like rebirth as Morocco's premier beach resort destination.</p>
                
                <p>This isn't just a drive-by tour - you'll have time to actually experience each location! Explore the colorful Souk El Had market where locals shop, climb to the Kasbah ruins for breathtaking panoramic views, stroll through the charming New Medina with its traditional architecture, and see the gleaming modern marina that showcases Agadir's prosperity. The <strong>Agadir city tour</strong> strikes the perfect balance between historical sites, cultural experiences, shopping opportunities, and modern attractions.</p>

                <h3>What Makes This Agadir Sightseeing Tour Special?</h3>
                <p>What sets our <strong>Agadir city tour</strong> apart is the local expertise. Your guide didn't just study Agadir's history from books - they or their family lived through the earthquake's aftermath and the city's rebirth. Hear personal stories, see family photos from before and after 1960, and understand how tragedy transformed into triumph. This personal connection brings history to life in a way generic tours simply cannot match.</p>
                
                <p>We keep groups small (maximum 15 people) to ensure you can ask questions, hear your guide clearly, and move efficiently between sites. The tour is paced perfectly - not rushed but not too slow. You'll have free time to shop at the souk, take photos from the Kasbah, and explore the marina. Our guide provides bargaining tips for the market, points out the best photo spots, and shares recommendations for restaurants and activities.</p>
                
                <p>This <strong>city tour Agadir half day</strong> is ideal for all travelers - families, couples, solo visitors, and groups. It's especially recommended for your first day in Agadir to get oriented, understand the city layout, and learn where everything is. After this tour, you'll navigate Agadir with confidence and have a deeper appreciation for this remarkable city's resilience and beauty.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Detailed Itinerary -->
            <div class="itinerary-section">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: #1F2937; margin-bottom: 30px;">Detailed Itinerary: Your Comprehensive Agadir City Tour</h2>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">Morning Tour: 9:00 AM | Afternoon Tour: 2:00 PM</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Hotel Pickup & Tour Introduction</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">We'll collect you from your hotel in Agadir in a comfortable, air-conditioned vehicle. Meet your expert local guide who will provide an overview of Agadir's fascinating history and what you'll discover today. Learn about the 1960 earthquake that changed everything as you begin your journey through the city.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+30 Minutes</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Agadir Kasbah Ruins & Panoramic Viewpoint</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Drive up to the hilltop Kasbah ruins - the only structure that partially survived the 1960 earthquake. Walk through the ancient fortress walls and restored gateway while your guide shares the dramatic earthquake story. Stand at the viewpoint for breathtaking panoramic photos of modern Agadir, the port, bay, and endless coastline. See the famous "God, Country, King" Arabic inscription on the hillside. Learn how the earthquake struck at 11:40 PM on February 29, 1960, lasting just 15 seconds but changing Agadir forever. This moving historical site sets the context for understanding the rest of the city.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+45 Minutes</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Souk El Had Market Exploration</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Visit the massive Souk El Had - North Africa's largest covered market with over 3,000 stalls! Enter through the grand gates into a sensory wonderland of colors, aromas, and sounds. The market is organized by sections: fresh produce and spices, traditional clothing and textiles, Moroccan crafts and souvenirs, household goods, and antiques. Enjoy 45 minutes of free time to browse, shop, and immerse yourself in authentic local life. Your guide provides bargaining tips (start at 50% of the asking price!) and points out the best stalls for argan oil, spices, and traditional goods. Try fresh Moroccan orange juice! Note: The souk is closed on Mondays - on those days we visit alternative markets or extend time at other sites.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+20 Minutes</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">New Medina (Medina Polizzi)</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Visit the charming New Medina, reconstructed after the earthquake by Italian architect Coco Polizzi. This beautiful traditional quarter showcases authentic Moroccan architecture with colorful painted walls, ornate doorways, and narrow winding streets. Explore artisan workshops where craftsmen create traditional pottery, leather goods, and woodwork. Browse small shops selling quality Moroccan crafts. The New Medina offers Instagram-worthy photo opportunities with its vibrant colors and traditional Moroccan aesthetic - a window into what old Agadir once looked like.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+20 Minutes</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Marina of Agadir & Waterfront</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Discover Agadir's stunning modern marina - a testament to the city's successful rebirth. Stroll along the beautiful waterfront lined with palm trees, admire luxury yachts and traditional fishing boats, and enjoy the Mediterranean-style architecture. The marina features upscale cafes, restaurants, and boutique shops. Take photos by the water with boats as backdrop. The contrast between the modern development and traditional fishing boats illustrates Agadir's blend of past and present. Time for a refreshing drink at a waterfront cafe if desired (own expense).</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+15 Minutes</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Corniche Beach Promenade Drive</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Cruise along Agadir's famous Corniche - a stunning 10-kilometer beach promenade lined with modern hotels, restaurants, and cafes. Your guide points out major landmarks, best beaches for swimming, recommended restaurants, and evening entertainment options. See the wide, clean boulevards designed for earthquake evacuation. Understand Agadir's master plan and urban development. Take in gorgeous ocean views and understand why Agadir is called "Morocco's Miami." This scenic drive showcases the city's successful transformation into a world-class beach resort.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">+15 Minutes (If Time Permits)</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Optional: Bird Valley Park or Additional Stop</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">If time allows, visit the peaceful Bird Valley Park (Vall√©e des Oiseaux) - a lush urban oasis in the city center. Home to exotic birds including flamingos, peacocks, and various waterfowl, this small zoo and botanical garden offers a tranquil escape. Alternatively, we may stop at the old Santa Cruz cathedral, the fishing port, or other points of interest based on the group's preferences and available time.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="itinerary-item">
                    <div class="itinerary-time">Total: 4 Hours | Return by 1:00 PM (Morning) or 6:00 PM (Afternoon)</div>
                    <h4 class="itinerary-title">Hotel Drop-off & Local Recommendations</h4>
                    <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Return to your hotel with a comprehensive understanding of Agadir's history, layout, and attractions. Your guide will answer any final questions and provide personalized recommendations for restaurants, activities, beaches, and evening entertainment based on your interests. Perfect timing - morning tours finish before lunch, afternoon tours end around dinner time. You'll now navigate Agadir like a local!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

