                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What happened in the 1960 Agadir earthquake?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>On February 29, 1960, a magnitude 5.7 earthquake struck Agadir at 11:40 PM, lasting just 15 seconds. It destroyed 90% of the city and tragically killed approximately 15,000 people (one-third of the population). The old city was buried and Agadir was rebuilt nearby. Our <strong>Agadir Kasbah and Medina visit</strong> includes this moving history explained with personal context by local guides.</p>
