                        <p>Only ruins remain after the earthquake. The Kasbah hilltop fortress (built 1572) partially survived due to its elevated location. The walls and entrance gateway have been partially restored as a historical memorial. The view from the Kasbah shows where old Agadir once stood (now the modern city) - a powerful, moving experience explained by your guide.</p>
